## How to Get These Values

### Supabase Connection URL
```
1. Login to Supabase Dashboard
2. Go to Settings → Database
3. Copy the "Connection pooling" connection string
4. Or go to Settings → API to get other credentials
5. Format: postgresql://user:password@host:port/database
```

### JWT Secret Generation
```bash
# Generate a random secure JWT secret (min 32 chars):
node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
```

### Render Backend Environment
```
1. Create account at https://render.com
2. Connect GitHub
3. Create new Web Service
4. Select your repo
5. In "Advanced" section, add environment variables
6. Copy from this template and replace placeholders
```

### Vercel Frontend Environment
```
1. Create account at https://vercel.com
2. Import GitHub project
3. In Project Settings → Environment Variables
4. Add the frontend variables from template
5. Redeploy to apply changes
```

